      "FacilityID": 39868,
      "SummaryText": "\n\nOUR WATER TREATMENT PLANT IS LOCATED ONE MILE SOUTH OF POTTSVILLE. THE FACILITY IS DESIGNED AND PERMITTED FOR 4 MGD. WE EMPLOY 4 FULL TIME EMPLOYEES, FROM 0700 TO 1530 HRS. 5 DAYS PER WEEK.  THE REST OF THE TIME THE PLANT IS ON AN ADT ALARM SYSTEM WHICH WILL CALL OUT PERSONEL AS NEEDED. \n\nTHE PLANT STAGES TWO(2),ONE (1) TON CYLINDERS AT ANY GIVEN TIME,ONE ON LINE THE OTHER ON STAND-BY CONTROLED BY AUTOMATIC CHANGE OVER VALVES WHEN ONE EMPTYS THE OTHER WILL TAKE OVER. ALSO ONE (1 )ONE TON CYLINDER IN STORAGE. THE DOSAGE BEING FED INTO OUR WATER SYSTEM IS CONTORLLED BY A MILL-AMP SIGNAL FROM A ROTORK FLOW METER DETERMINED BY THE RATE SET AT THE CHLORINIATOR BY ONE OF THE OPERATORS.THE POST CHLORINE RESIDUAL IS MONITORED BY A WALLACE & TIERNAN ANALYZER AND CHART RECORDER WHICH IS ALSO WIRED INTO THE PLANT ALARM SYSTEM FOR 24 HOURS/DAY, 7 DAYS / WEEK PROTECTION. \n\nALSO THE CHLORINE SYSTEM IS DESIGNED TO SHUT OFF IN THE EVENT OF A MALFUNCTION. THE CHLORINE IS LOCATED IN AN ISOLATED ROOM EQUIPPED WITH A VENTILATION FAN AND A LEAK DETECTOR WIRED TO THE PLANT ALARM SYSTEM. \n\nOUR PLANT ALSO HAS AN OFF-SITE RELEASE PLAN APPROVE BY THE LOCAL EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT AGENCY. TO SATISFY THE REQUIREMENTS OF THE FEDERAL BIOTERRORISM ACT WE ALSO COMPLETED AND SUBMITTED OUR VULNERABILITY ASSESSMENT AND UP DATED OUR EMERGENCY RESPONSE PLAN BASED ON OUR VULNERABILITY ASSESSMENT .\n\nIF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS FEEL FREE TO CONTACT ME AT 570-385-2841, OR travisjack@schuylkillhaven.org"
    }
